# CAMEL + KAFKA RULES

## 1. MESSAGE SAFETY
- Always assume messages may be duplicated
- Enforce idempotency

---

## 2. ERROR HANDLING
- Always define onException
- Return structured error (JSON)

---

## 3. STREAM PROCESSING
- Avoid blocking operations
- Prefer async/non-blocking

---

## 4. KAFKA DESIGN
- Never assume single partition
- Design for parallelism
- Use key-based partitioning when needed

---

## 5. CAMEL BEST PRACTICES
- Use EIPs instead of custom logic
- Avoid large processors
- Prefer:
  - split
  - aggregate
  - throttle
  - circuitBreaker

---

## 6. EXTERNAL CALLS
- Always define timeout
- Always define retry policy

---

## 7. SECURITY
- Never log message payload if sensitive
